WEBVTT

00:00.100 --> 00:01.748
Previously on "switched at birth"...

00:01.768 --> 00:04.067
- Are you okay?
- This is your fault.

00:04.088 --> 00:06.518
He died of an aneurysm.

00:06.538 --> 00:08.339
Why are you defending her?

00:08.373 --> 00:09.474
Bay: It's hereditary.

00:09.508 --> 00:10.541
That doesn't necessarily mean...

00:10.576 --> 00:12.310
That's there's a ticking time bomb

00:12.344 --> 00:14.245
in my brain that could
go off at any moment?

00:14.484 --> 00:17.473
_

00:17.493 --> 00:21.041
_

00:21.061 --> 00:23.166
Do you know a guy named Emmett Bledsoe?

00:23.186 --> 00:25.260
- No.
- He thinks he's in a relationship with you

00:25.280 --> 00:27.587
and that your name is Mandy Starling.

00:27.607 --> 00:29.611
Daphne, this is Wes.

00:29.631 --> 00:31.721
We're just breaking ground on
the east riverside project.

00:31.741 --> 00:33.396
Look, if you're really pissed at your ma

00:33.416 --> 00:35.568
and you need her to know,
then you gotta show her.

00:35.588 --> 00:38.473
Daphne:
There's a groundbreaking ceremony tomorrow.

00:39.124 --> 00:41.017
Bad girl, huh?

00:48.079 --> 00:51.165
John: So you got the full payout
on Angelo's insurance, huh?

00:51.185 --> 00:52.883
You don't think I should have?

00:52.917 --> 00:55.819
Oh, I'm not saying that at all.
You deserve every penny.

00:55.853 --> 00:57.973
I just, you know, figured they'd try

00:57.993 --> 01:01.044
some kind of pre-existing-
condition nonsense.

01:01.308 --> 01:02.392
They didn't.

01:02.426 --> 01:04.394
Now I just have to figure
out what to do with it.

01:04.428 --> 01:05.428
Hmm.

01:05.462 --> 01:08.565
So I'm thinking...
College fund, investments?

01:08.599 --> 01:10.467
Well, I'll put you in touch
with my financial guy,

01:10.501 --> 01:12.135
he can run you through some options.

01:12.169 --> 01:13.851
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

01:14.332 --> 01:16.070
I hope Bay needs a college fund.

01:16.090 --> 01:19.074
I think she'll try for art school again.
She just needs some time.

01:19.094 --> 01:20.602
(Door opens)
Hmm.

01:20.622 --> 01:23.875
Well, we got one on the right path.
(Chuckles)

01:23.895 --> 01:26.776
I thought you were going out for a run.

01:26.796 --> 01:30.193
- I didn't feel like it.
- Um, I should get going.

01:31.154 --> 01:34.726
I will... I will call my financial guy
later today, okay?

01:34.746 --> 01:37.129
- What's going on?
- Um,

01:37.414 --> 01:40.392
Angelo's life insurance policy
came through.

01:41.795 --> 01:43.189
How much?

01:43.209 --> 01:45.398
- One million.
- And you're taking it?

01:45.418 --> 01:47.267
John: Wait, wait, sweetie,
that's what it's for.

01:47.287 --> 01:50.035
To take care of you, and bay, and Regina.

01:50.055 --> 01:51.993
There's a lot to think through.

01:52.013 --> 01:54.276
- Thanks so much for your help.
- No problem, any time.

01:54.296 --> 01:55.934
Okay.

02:00.104 --> 02:02.650
Like John said,

02:02.670 --> 02:04.512
it's for all of us.

02:04.532 --> 02:07.118
I don't want it. It's blood money.

02:07.138 --> 02:08.880
How is it blood money?

02:08.900 --> 02:11.560
Angelo is dead because of you

02:11.580 --> 02:14.607
and now you get a million dollars?

02:18.401 --> 02:20.800
(Door opens, closes)
(Sighs)

02:23.888 --> 02:25.607
(Phone clicking)

02:28.814 --> 02:31.743
_

02:32.698 --> 02:35.450
Bay: So basically, this could kill me.

02:36.253 --> 02:38.417
Where there's a family
history of aneurysms,

02:38.437 --> 02:40.365
there is a higher risk factor.

02:40.385 --> 02:43.170
But it's by no means a guarantee...

02:43.190 --> 02:44.525
Especially at your age.

02:44.545 --> 02:48.020
Even though my aunt died of one
at exactly my age?

02:48.040 --> 02:51.242
That's why it's a good thing
we're getting the M.R.I. today.

02:52.111 --> 02:53.802
So, uh...

02:54.382 --> 02:57.999
If you find something, then what do we do?

02:58.019 --> 03:00.469
Those are things I can discuss
with you and your family

03:00.489 --> 03:02.281
when we get the results.

03:02.417 --> 03:03.745
Okay.

03:03.765 --> 03:06.192
You have someone here with you today?

03:06.416 --> 03:09.617
I kind of just want to keep this
off the radar for right now.

03:09.651 --> 03:11.775
That's not what I would recommend.

03:11.795 --> 03:13.435
But it's legal.

03:13.455 --> 03:15.952
Since I'm 18,
I have the right to confidential treatment.

03:15.972 --> 03:19.393
Bay, I know this is scary.

03:19.428 --> 03:22.202
But you will do better
with a support system.

03:23.344 --> 03:25.898
The problem is my support system

03:25.918 --> 03:27.268
just went through hell with Angelo,

03:27.302 --> 03:29.036
so until we know for sure that this is

03:29.071 --> 03:31.072
something to worry about...

03:31.106 --> 03:34.493
I would really rather not put them
through anything else right now.

03:35.312 --> 03:36.563
Okay.

03:37.431 --> 03:39.442
You ready for the scan?

03:39.826 --> 03:41.482
As ready as I'll ever be.

03:42.035 --> 03:44.381
S03E19
You Will Not Escape

03:44.401 --> 03:47.359
sync and corrected by ninh
www.addic7ed.com

03:51.454 --> 03:54.028
No, I understand. Absolutely.

03:54.062 --> 03:56.021
Guys, I need to jump off.

03:56.281 --> 03:57.775
Yeah, okay, send me the notes.

03:57.795 --> 03:58.962
Thanks.
(Beeps)

03:58.982 --> 04:01.024
(Sighs) Sounds like you're back
in the swing of things.

04:01.044 --> 04:04.522
Yeah, I don't know why
Wes puts me on calls with contractors.

04:04.542 --> 04:08.228
I'm like, "guys, I do interiors.
Call me when it's done."

04:08.248 --> 04:10.226
Well, it's nice he wants your input.

04:10.246 --> 04:11.802
- Yeah...
- Guess what?!

04:11.822 --> 04:14.073
I got invited to go to New York tomorrow.

04:14.093 --> 04:16.605
My publisher is throwing a party
for all the new releases.

04:16.625 --> 04:17.966
Here is the fun part...

04:17.986 --> 04:20.587
they offered me a plus
one for everything...

04:20.622 --> 04:22.856
flight, hotel, everything.

04:22.891 --> 04:24.715
Great, I can water plants

04:24.735 --> 04:26.180
or do whatever you need.

04:26.200 --> 04:29.288
Actually,
I was hoping that you would come with me.

04:29.308 --> 04:31.532
John hates New York and...

04:31.566 --> 04:32.933
to be honest, I'm a little nervous.

04:32.967 --> 04:35.381
There's gonna be all
these fancy writers and...

04:35.401 --> 04:37.818
I could use some company.

04:37.838 --> 04:39.740
(Sighs) That's really sweet of you

04:39.774 --> 04:42.416
but I'm still kind of in the thick of it.

04:42.436 --> 04:43.944
It's one day.

04:43.978 --> 04:44.922
One.

04:44.942 --> 04:46.238
Please.

04:50.683 --> 04:53.654
Excellent! I'll email you the info.

