- Hey.
- Hey.

11:43.012 --> 11:44.405
Um...

11:49.837 --> 11:51.964
It's been a while since I've been here.

11:51.984 --> 11:55.252
Yeah, you know,
some kids thought it'd be cool,

11:55.272 --> 11:56.488
but it's kinda lame.

11:56.508 --> 11:58.486
Well, this should help.

12:01.468 --> 12:03.297
Awesome, thanks.

12:03.317 --> 12:05.017
You got it.

12:08.057 --> 12:10.501
He's asking how we know each other.

12:10.521 --> 12:12.809
From East Riverside.

12:12.829 --> 12:15.142
Do you guys want some beers?

12:15.162 --> 12:18.351
You better be cool with that.
You don't want us getting kicked out.

12:20.479 --> 12:23.730
_

12:24.020 --> 12:27.234
Um, do you want to go ride the boats?

12:27.254 --> 12:28.557
Um, maybe later.

12:28.577 --> 12:31.362
I think we're gonna find
a place to just hang.

12:31.585 --> 12:34.564
Can I talk to you for a second?
Great, thanks.

12:35.643 --> 12:38.433
Is that who I think it is?

12:38.467 --> 12:40.260
I don't know. Who do you think it is?

12:40.280 --> 12:42.604
The guy who threw a brick
through Regina's window

12:42.638 --> 12:46.084
and then called her a whore
when we asked him about it.

12:47.412 --> 12:49.795
I invited him. He's cool.

12:50.167 --> 12:51.955
"He's cool"?

12:52.861 --> 12:54.777
Turns out we have some things in common.

12:54.797 --> 12:58.003
Seriously,
this is your new way to piss off Regina?

12:58.023 --> 13:01.156
Hanging out with the thug
who destroyed her property?

13:01.190 --> 13:02.743
Oh, very mature.

13:02.763 --> 13:03.830
He's not a thug.

13:03.850 --> 13:06.428
Couldn't you try to be
a little less obvious?

13:06.448 --> 13:09.377
You have no idea what you're talking about.

13:14.036 --> 13:15.484
(Idle chatter)

13:15.504 --> 13:17.472
Here we go.

13:17.506 --> 13:19.273
Here it is.

13:19.823 --> 13:21.131
What do you think?

13:21.151 --> 13:24.412
- (Kathryn gasps)
- Regina: Ooh, look at you.

13:24.897 --> 13:28.128
Lydia: Oh, I envy you two,
making a girls weekend of it.

13:28.148 --> 13:29.754
Kathryn: Oh,
thank you so much for including me.

13:29.774 --> 13:33.464
Oh, of course. I love seeing
the expense account put to good use.

13:33.484 --> 13:35.308
Kathryn, nice dress.

13:35.328 --> 13:39.043
Oh, I was just trying not to feel
like the out-of-town aunt.

13:39.063 --> 13:41.785
Oh, please. No one here bites...

13:41.805 --> 13:44.602
Except possibly Andrea Askowitz.

13:44.622 --> 13:47.407
(Gasps) Oh, I love her.

13:47.427 --> 13:50.075
She wrote this hilarious
memoir about her mother

13:50.095 --> 13:53.115
- called "Battle Axe."
- Ooh, no wonder she bites.

13:53.135 --> 13:55.590
Well, she did a new bio on Edith Wharton.

13:55.610 --> 13:57.945
And she is right over there.

13:57.979 --> 14:00.257
(Boisterous laughter)

14:00.277 --> 14:02.683
Her little algonquin table.

14:02.717 --> 14:04.965
I can take you over.

14:05.219 --> 14:07.730
I think I need to work up the nerve first.

14:07.750 --> 14:09.356
(Laughs) Well, that's what a bar is for.

14:09.390 --> 14:11.458
- What can I get you?
- Oh, nothing for me, thanks.

14:11.492 --> 14:12.626
Oh.

14:12.851 --> 14:14.361
Oh, excuse me.

14:14.395 --> 14:16.544
Robin's giving me the rescue signal.

14:16.564 --> 14:17.681
Um...

14:18.538 --> 14:20.441
Robin is her girlfriend.

14:20.461 --> 14:22.439
- Oh.
- Oh no, thank you.

14:22.459 --> 14:23.737
(Sighs)

14:23.757 --> 14:26.517
I am so sorry
this is such a boozy event.

14:26.537 --> 14:29.161
Well, it is a bunch of writers.

14:29.181 --> 14:30.439
I'm fine,

14:30.459 --> 14:33.479
and it's fun to see you in your element.

14:33.499 --> 14:36.664
Ah, well, I'm not sure I am.

14:39.648 --> 14:42.701
Deep fried kale?
Doesn't that defeat the purpose?

14:42.850 --> 14:44.530
_

14:44.550 --> 14:46.366
_

14:46.386 --> 14:47.503
(Scoffs)

14:54.096 --> 14:58.030
Um, maybe we should try the taco stand.

14:58.366 --> 15:00.592
_

15:00.612 --> 15:03.670
Okay, well,
why don't I hold our place in line

15:03.690 --> 15:07.053
and you go get me a veggie burrito?

15:07.984 --> 15:09.609
_

15:20.452 --> 15:22.132
Hey, I remember you.

15:22.152 --> 15:24.391
You came to see me at my school.

15:24.411 --> 15:26.079
Oh, yeah, right.

15:26.099 --> 15:29.207
Jennifer. You were asking about that thing
with my cousin Matthew.

15:29.227 --> 15:31.875
Oh, yeah,
I can't believe you remember that.

15:31.895 --> 15:34.208
No, totally. It turned into a huge thing.

15:34.228 --> 15:35.887
My mom and my aunt got in a big fight

15:35.907 --> 15:38.357
and then they made Matthew
show us all the stuff he wrote.

15:38.377 --> 15:41.653
It was so crazy.
He used me to trick that poor guy.

15:41.988 --> 15:44.760
Eh, well, he was pretty confused I'm sure.

15:44.780 --> 15:46.263
It's so weird that you're here.

15:46.283 --> 15:48.844
- Senior ditch day.
- Oh, cool, us too.

15:48.864 --> 15:51.835
- Okay, well I should probably go...
- Hey, is that guy here?

15:51.855 --> 15:53.458
Emmett?

15:53.493 --> 15:55.794
I... don't think so.

15:55.829 --> 15:58.118
(Dejected) Oh, too bad.

15:58.138 --> 16:00.365
I mean,
I'm sure it was a total nightmare for him,

16:00.400 --> 16:03.302
but he was so sweet to that Mandy girl.

16:03.336 --> 16:06.648
It almost made me wish I was her
after I read all that stuff he wrote.

16:06.668 --> 16:09.341
- Really?
- Oh man, he loved her,

16:09.375 --> 16:10.867
and she wasn't even real.

16:10.887 --> 16:13.145
It's like... tragic.

16:13.791 --> 16:15.147
After I read that stuff he wrote,

16:15.181 --> 16:17.321
I kind of dumped this guy I was seeing,
Chad,

16:17.341 --> 16:19.393
'cause it's like,
if I can't have a connection like that,

16:19.413 --> 16:21.676
then what's the point? You know?

16:21.696 --> 16:22.533
Right.

16:22.553 --> 16:25.506
I hope he finds someone that deserves him.

16:25.643 --> 16:27.756
Anyway, good to see you.

16:28.413 --> 16:29.758
You too.

16:29.778 --> 16:31.119
Ciao.

17:02.837 --> 17:03.765
- (Nacho sighs)
- Hey.

17:03.785 --> 17:05.056
I got you guys some burgers.

17:05.076 --> 17:08.776
Oh, cool, thanks. Here, you guys want some?

17:09.273 --> 17:11.098
So sweet.

17:11.117 --> 17:12.798
(Laughs)

17:13.281 --> 17:14.374
Damn, girl.

17:14.394 --> 17:17.518
Hey, I can't help it if I'm a good shot.

17:18.333 --> 17:19.752
Oh. (Chuckles)

17:21.036 --> 17:22.351
Who's that?

17:22.371 --> 17:24.980
- Oh, that's Romy.
- Well, no, I know that.

17:25.000 --> 17:26.518
I just...

17:26.538 --> 17:29.913
Like, are you here with me? Or...

17:30.198 --> 17:32.633
Look, it was cool the other night,

17:32.667 --> 17:35.274
but, you know,
it's not like we're together.

17:36.229 --> 17:38.686
No, I know.

17:39.456 --> 17:41.141
You wanna go hit the tank?

17:42.204 --> 17:44.586
- Maybe later.
- Cool.

17:44.810 --> 17:46.423
Could you grab me a beer?

17:46.808 --> 17:48.384
Rigo, you're up.

17:53.050 --> 17:54.712
- (Ball clangs)
- Nacho: Yeah!

17:54.732 --> 17:56.661
(Nacho laughs)

17:57.542 --> 17:59.478
Oh, that was... come on, now.

17:59.498 --> 18:01.608
You can't throw it like a girl.

18:01.628 --> 18:03.197
(Piano music playing)

18:04.383 --> 18:06.311
This is actually pretty good.

18:06.331 --> 18:08.594
- And I hate poetry.
- Well, let's go and meet her.

18:08.614 --> 18:11.939
And maybe I'll work up the nerve to talk
to Andrea Askowitz.

18:11.973 --> 18:13.923
Kathryn Kennish.

18:13.943 --> 18:14.875
Yes.

18:14.909 --> 18:18.178
Chris Washburn, chapter eight.

18:18.198 --> 18:21.008
Oh, hi. How are you doing?

18:21.028 --> 18:22.583
I'm doing good.

18:22.617 --> 18:25.781
Not the golden God I used to be,
you flatterer.

18:26.178 --> 18:29.021
Uh... well, you know...

18:29.041 --> 18:31.486
You know, I work in legal
and I just about fell out of my chair

18:31.506 --> 18:34.431
when I saw your name on the new releases.

18:34.451 --> 18:37.819
Course, you'll always be
Katie Dixon to me.

18:37.839 --> 18:40.644
That's me.
Katie Dixon. (Chuckles)

18:40.780 --> 18:42.127
So...

18:42.147 --> 18:45.498
You wrote it even hotter than I remembered.

18:47.359 --> 18:50.206
You know,
we should have snuck into that sleeper car.

18:50.226 --> 18:52.832
It would have been
better than the bathroom.

18:54.005 --> 18:56.412
- Oh...
- It's... it's okay.

18:57.206 --> 18:59.730
Your secret's safe with me.

18:59.750 --> 19:02.833
Once these people get wind
of a juicy tidbit like that...

19:02.853 --> 19:04.265
