28:18.676 --> 28:21.385
Hey, what the hell was that?

28:21.762 --> 28:22.506
Back off.

28:22.541 --> 28:24.342
Mary Beth is my friend,

28:24.376 --> 28:25.842
so no, I'm not gonna back off.

28:25.862 --> 28:27.691
What, your thug wasn't enough for you?

28:27.711 --> 28:29.503
Yeah, that's not racist.

28:29.523 --> 28:31.575
And you using that guy like a prop

28:31.595 --> 28:34.251
to piss off Regina, that's not riseither?

28:34.271 --> 28:36.187
Look, this has nothing to do with you.

28:36.221 --> 28:37.221
Just stay out of it.

28:37.255 --> 28:38.975
You punishing my mother

28:38.995 --> 28:41.800
for my father dying has
nothing to do with me?

28:41.820 --> 28:44.701
- This is between me and Regina.
- No, it's not!

28:44.721 --> 28:45.963
We are all in this, okay?

28:45.998 --> 28:49.310
And we are all getting tired
of you lashing out at her.

28:49.330 --> 28:52.597
Sorry if I'm not getting
back to grill night fast enough for you.

28:52.617 --> 28:54.210
You know what, you are not the only one

28:54.230 --> 28:58.084
going through stuff,
so stop acting like a little brat.

29:04.404 --> 29:06.402
Exactly, exactly.

29:08.097 --> 29:09.596
Excuse me, Ms. Askowitz?

29:09.616 --> 29:11.266
- Uh-huh?
- I'm Kathryn Kennish

29:11.300 --> 29:13.943
and it is an honor to meet you.

29:13.963 --> 29:15.937
Oh, hello.

29:15.971 --> 29:18.212
Right, sit down, please.

29:18.232 --> 29:19.775
Go.

29:19.795 --> 29:21.111
(Whispers) I'm sorry.

29:24.190 --> 29:26.635
(Clears throat)
(Sighs heavily)

29:27.181 --> 29:29.369
Kathryn loved your
memoir about your mother.

29:29.389 --> 29:30.995
- Oh.
- Kathryn: "Battle Axe"

29:31.015 --> 29:32.993
was so smart and funny

29:33.013 --> 29:36.360
and so sadly relatable.

29:36.782 --> 29:38.263
I mean, not that your mom was sad...

29:38.283 --> 29:39.839
Trust me, she was sad.

29:39.859 --> 29:41.485
(Laughs)
(Nervous chuckles)

29:41.746 --> 29:44.992
Oh, I'm so sorry. This is Regina Vasquez.

29:45.489 --> 29:48.633
I wanted to tell you how much I enjoyed
"Batter Up."

29:48.653 --> 29:49.800
- You read it?
- Mm-hmm.

29:49.820 --> 29:53.783
What I wanted to ask you is if I could
include it in my next syllabus.

29:53.803 --> 29:56.924
I do a seminar on Jane
Austen in popular context.

29:56.944 --> 29:59.220
Wait a second, did you just say Jane Austen

29:59.240 --> 30:01.479
and "Batter Up" in the same sentence?

30:01.499 --> 30:02.409
Mm-hmm, I think there's

30:02.429 --> 30:07.087
I think there's some really playful
parallels between regency England

30:07.107 --> 30:10.277
and all that encoded, gender-specific stuff

30:10.297 --> 30:12.250
that you write about in pro athletics.

30:12.270 --> 30:15.610
Plus your book's hot,
so the undergrads will actually read it.

30:15.630 --> 30:17.298
(Laughs)

30:19.098 --> 30:21.583
Thanks for coming all this way.

30:21.603 --> 30:23.090
It's okay.

30:23.110 --> 30:25.323
My aunt can come pick me up.

30:31.268 --> 30:32.830
You okay?

30:33.981 --> 30:35.747
How do you deal with it?

30:35.767 --> 30:39.184
With your mom and everything
she's done to you?

30:40.438 --> 30:44.662
I guess I just tell myself
she's not really my mom.

30:44.682 --> 30:47.206
My mom took care of me when I was little...

30:47.330 --> 30:49.863
threw me birthday parties,

30:49.897 --> 30:52.319
sang Lionel Ritchie to torture me.

30:55.336 --> 30:57.437
So you forgive her?

30:59.707 --> 31:02.809
It's more like I wait for her to come back.

31:08.298 --> 31:11.864
I don't know who my mom is anymore.
(Sobbing)

31:11.884 --> 31:14.138
Anyway, thanks for the ride.

31:17.489 --> 31:18.648
Hey.

31:18.668 --> 31:19.760
Here.

31:22.056 --> 31:24.034
I know you got a lot going on,

31:24.054 --> 31:27.216
but if you need something,
you let me know, okay?

31:28.296 --> 31:29.847
Yeah.

31:30.430 --> 31:32.329
I see you later.

31:41.527 --> 31:42.711
Score!

31:42.731 --> 31:45.089
- I made friends with the caterer.
- Ah-ha!

31:45.387 --> 31:47.184
You know what? This is crazy.
People are tweeting

31:47.204 --> 31:49.413
about my open marriage.

31:49.904 --> 31:54.091
Chris Washburn. What was I thinking?

31:54.265 --> 31:58.763
You know, um, I slept with Angelo
the first day I met him.

31:58.783 --> 32:00.376
But then again, who didn't?

32:00.396 --> 32:01.748
(Both laughing)

32:04.952 --> 32:06.886
(Laughing continues)

32:16.540 --> 32:17.971
(Sighs)

32:18.294 --> 32:20.726
That's the first time I've laughed since...

32:22.327 --> 32:23.895
You're allowed.

32:23.915 --> 32:25.479
(Breathes deeply)

32:25.499 --> 32:27.129
Thank you for this.

32:27.464 --> 32:28.951
I really needed it.

32:30.862 --> 32:32.773
You're gonna be okay.

32:32.793 --> 32:34.833
I don't think so.

32:34.853 --> 32:36.620
Daphne hates me.

32:36.640 --> 32:39.093
No, she doesn't.

32:39.113 --> 32:41.518
It's just easier for Daphne to blame you

32:41.538 --> 32:45.397
than to deal with how random
and cruel it was.

32:45.417 --> 32:47.652
Well, it sucks.

32:47.686 --> 32:49.542
Part of being a mom.

32:49.562 --> 32:50.922
You give 'em everything,

32:50.956 --> 32:53.711
they write a book about you called
"Battle Axe."

32:55.002 --> 32:57.893
I just wanna get back
to some kind of normal.

32:57.913 --> 33:00.398
And if it takes giving that money back...

33:00.433 --> 33:01.700
Whoa.

33:01.720 --> 33:04.671
That money is your ticket to independence.

33:04.691 --> 33:06.329
Pay off all your debts,

33:06.349 --> 33:09.307
put most of it away and then do something

33:09.341 --> 33:12.077
that makes you and Daphne happy.

33:15.080 --> 33:16.520
Yeah.

33:17.488 --> 33:20.143
Bay, thanks for coming in.

33:20.163 --> 33:22.187
Well, you know, possible mortality...

33:22.221 --> 33:23.634
thought I'd make time for it.

33:23.654 --> 33:25.156
I didn't mean to alarm you.

33:25.191 --> 33:28.308
I just find it best to go
over everything in person.

33:30.542 --> 33:31.741
So...

33:32.051 --> 33:33.098
So...

33:33.132 --> 33:35.270
Your M.R.I. came back negative.

33:35.290 --> 33:37.983
We found no presence of
aneurysms at this time.

33:38.003 --> 33:39.998
So I'm gonna be okay. That's it?

33:40.018 --> 33:42.044
You should just focus on living your life

33:42.064 --> 33:44.533
- and stay away from the Internet.
- (Laughs)

33:47.052 --> 33:49.671
I feel like you gave me my life back.

33:51.532 --> 33:53.105
Thank you.

33:53.125 --> 33:54.763
